OL,3,CUK Government told it 'could have gone
OL,4,Cfurther' on North Sea windfall tax
OL,6,FBut she said: "The UK Government
OL,7,Fcould've gone further. Keeping the
OL,8,Fenergy profits levy in place for
OL,9,Fanother four years risks accelerating
OL,10,Fthe industry's decline and job losses,
OL,11,Feven though it's well known that the
OL,12,FUK will need oil and gas in its energy
OL,13,Fmix for decades to come as we
OL,14,Ftransition to net zero."
OL,16,FShe added that the committee was yet
OL,17,Fto see "concrete evidence" of delivery
OL,18,Fon the UK Government's clean energy
OL,19,Fcommitments.
